Homeland Security Advisor Dr. Liz Sherwood-Randall led a delegation to Panama and Colombia to address the humanitarian situation and growing migration challenge in the Darien jungle region. In Panama, Sherwood-Randall met with President Laurentino Cortizo to discuss reducing irregular migratory flows and expanding safe legal pathways for migration. She also appreciated Panama's efforts in offering Temporary Protected Status to migrants. In Colombia, Sherwood-Randall met with Foreign Minister √Ålvaro Leyva to discuss initiatives to disrupt transnational criminal groups exploiting migrants. She expressed appreciation for cooperation in opening new U.S. Secure Mobility Offices in Colombia and emphasized the need to address the humanitarian and environmental crisis in the Darien region. The delegation conducted field visits to assess how the United States can support regional partners in reducing irregular migration and providing humanitarian relief.